{{infobox person | name = Bazlur Rahman Badal | native_name = বজলুর রহমান বাদল | native_name_lang = bn | image = Bazlur Rahman Badal.jpg | alt = Bazlur Rahman Badal was invited as a honorable guest on ''The Independence Day of Bangladesh'' celebration hosted by Rajshahi College. | caption = Badal at [[Rajshahi College]] (2017) | nationality = Bangladeshi | occupation = Dancer | birth_date = 1921/1922 | birth_place = [[Jalpaiguri district]], [[Bengal Presidency]], [[British India]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2018|08|19|1922|df=y}} | death_place = [[Rajshahi]], Bangladesh | awards= [[Independence Day Award]] (2017) }}
'''Bazlur Rahman Badal''' (1921/1922 – 19 August 2018)<ref name=death>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/news/arts-entertainment/bazlur-rahman-badal-passes-away-1623136|title=Bazlur Rahman Badal passes away|date=2018-08-20|work=The Daily Star|access-date=2018-08-19|language=en}}</ref> was a Bangladeshi dancer. He was awarded [[Shilpakala Padak]] in 2014<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/arts-entertainment/event/shilpakala-padak-2014-conferred-3039|title=Shilpakala Padak 2014 conferred|date= February 21, 2015|accessdate=February 25, 2017|newspaper=The Daily Star}}</ref> and [[Independence Day Award]] in 2017 in the dance category by the [[Government of Bangladesh]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/frontpage/independence-award-2017-announced-1362568|title=Independence Award 2017 announced|date=February 17, 2017|accessdate=February 25, 2017|newspaper=The Daily Star}}</ref>
==Career== After the [[partition of India]] in 1947, Badal migrated to [[Rangpur District|Rangpur]] and eventually to [[Rajshahi]] where he began his dance training under the guidance of his first teacher, known as ''Dukhu Master''.<ref name=death/> He provided dance lessons to the students in Rajshahi's Shilpakala Academy.<ref name=death/>
Badal specializes in folk dance. He became notable for his dance composition of the poem ''[[Bidrohi]]'' of [[Kazi Nazrul Islam]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/2004/03/04/d40304140293.htm|author=Novera Deepita|date=March 4, 2004|accessdate=February 25, 2017|newspaper=The Daily Star|title=Bangladesh Shilpakala Academy honours seven performers}}</ref> He served as the president of Bangladesh Nritya Shilpi Sangstha ([[Rajshahi]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news-detail-231195|title=National Dance Festival kicks off today at Shilpakala Academy|date=April 23, 2012|accessdate=February 25, 2017|newspaper=The Daily Star}}</ref>
