A '''specific legacy''' (or '''specific bequest''') is a [[Testamentary disposition|testamentary gift]] of a precisely identifiable object, distinguished from all other things of the same kind — such as, a [[Gift (law)|gift]] of a particular piece of [[Jewellery|jewelry]].
